issue.title: Docs: Incorrect venn diagram for anti right join
issue.body:
## Steps to reproduce

1. Open the PostgreSQL Joins tutorial page in Neon docs: https://neon.com/postgresql/postgresql-tutorial/postgresql-joins
2. Scroll to the **Right Anti-Join** section.
3. Observe the diagram shown.

## Expected result

The diagram should highlight **only the portion of the right table (T2) that does not overlap with the left table (T1)**, since Right Anti-Join returns rows from the right table without matches in the left table.

## Actual result

The diagram shown for **Right Anti-Join** is the same as the **Right Join** diagram, which incorrectly highlights the entire right table including the overlap.

## Environment

* Browser: zen-browser
* OS: kubuntu
* Page: https://neon.com/postgresql/postgresql-tutorial/postgresql-joins

+(oracle-tutorial)=
+# Load data from Oracle into CrateDB
+
+The tutorial will walk you through starting the [Oracle Database] and CrateDB,
+inserting a record into Oracle, loading data into a CrateDB table,
+and validating that the data has been stored successfully.
+The data transfer is supported by the
+{ref}`CrateDB Toolkit Ingestr I/O <ctk:ingestr>` data pipeline elements.
+
+## Prerequisites
+
+Docker is used for running all components. This approach works consistently
+across Linux, macOS, and Windows. Alternatively, you can use Podman.
+
+Create a shared network.
+```shell
+docker network create cratedb-demo
+```
+
+Start CrateDB.
+```shell
+docker run --rm --name=cratedb --network=cratedb-demo \
+  --publish=4200:4200 --publish=5432:5432 \
+  docker.io/crate -Cdiscovery.type=single-node
+```
+
+Start Oracle DBMS.
+```shell
+docker run --rm --name=oracle --network=cratedb-demo \
+  --publish=1521:1521 \
+  --env=ORACLE_PASSWORD=secret \
+  docker.io/gvenzl/oracle-free:23-slim
+```
+
+Prepare shortcuts for the CrateDB shell, CrateDB Toolkit, and the Oracle client
+programs.
+
+::::{tab-set}
+
+:::{tab-item} Linux and macOS
+To make the settings persistent, add them to your shell profile (`~/.profile`).
+```shell
+alias crash="docker run --rm -it --network=cratedb-demo ghcr.io/crate/cratedb-toolkit crash"
+alias ctk-ingest="docker run --rm -i --network=cratedb-demo ghcr.io/crate/cratedb-toolkit-ingest ctk"
+alias sqlplus="docker run --rm -it --network=cratedb-demo --volume=$(PWD):/demo --env=ORACLE_PASSWORD=secret --entrypoint= docker.io/gvenzl/oracle-free:23-slim sqlplus"
+```

- Updated calculateFileHash to accept a customizable hashChunkSize parameter for improved MD5 calculation.

pull_request.body: This PR leverages the resource primitive from MCPServers and introduces a new ResourceManager to enable using resources within the application. The core idea of resources is to enable pulling data/information based on the paths and references provided by the MCPServer. We extended it primarily in our client to enable referencing it as context for LLM to use when referenced by the user but can be extended to other app functionalities as well. We also add functionality to reference resources in the webui using `@` for MCPServers that do expose resources.
